verbose_text: However, the expression levels of phosphorylated Akt and phosphorylated eNOS were significantly lower in the mice with MI compared with the sham operated group (P < 0.05); treatment with muscone increased the phosphorylation of Akt (1.968 +/-0.2110 vs. 1.286 +/-0.04034; MD 0.6825 +/-0.2149; 95% CI 0.08610-1.279; P = 0.0336) and phosphorylated eNOS (2.347 +/-0.2729 vs. 1.537 +/-0.1645; MD 0.8095 +/-0.3186; 95% CI 0.02995-1.589; P = 0.044) compared to the untreated group (XREF_FIG).
